BASIC LINUX COMMANDS FOR DIRECTORY OPERATIONS,DISPLAYING DIRECTORY,STRUCTURE IN TREE FORMAT etc..



1.Create a directory
hwlab5@hwlab5:~$ mkdir newfolder

2.Remove a directory
hwlab5@hwlab5:~$ rmdir test

3.List the directory
hwlab5@hwlab5:~$ ls
8086       Downloads         libgraph-1.0.2         newfolder  Sreerenjini
Arjun      examples.desktop  libgraph-1.0.2.tar.gz  Pictures   Templates
Desktop    first.sh          minnu                  Public     test
Documents  JoelJS2R          Music                  rahulc     Videos

4.List the hidden directory
hwlab5@hwlab5:~$ ls -a
.              examples.desktop       .profile
..             first.sh               Public
8086           .gconf                 rahulc
Arjun          .ICEauthority          Sreerenjini
.bash_history  JoelJS2R               .sudo_as_admin_successful
.bash_logout   libgraph-1.0.2         Templates
.bashrc        libgraph-1.0.2.tar.gz  test
.cache         .local                 Videos
.compiz        minnu                  .Xauthority
.config        .mozilla               .xinputrc
Desktop        Music                  .xsession-errors
Documents      .nano                  .xsession-errors.old
.dosbox        newfolder
Downloads      Pictures

5.Change the directory
hwlab5@hwlab5:~$ cd newfolder
hwlab5@hwlab5:~/newfolder$ 

6.Create a blank file
hwlab5@hwlab5:~/newfolder$ touch file1
hwlab5@hwlab5:~/newfolder$ ls
file1



7.Print the working directory
hwlab5@hwlab5:~/newfolder$ pwd
/home/hwlab5/newfolder

8.Creating a file with data
hwlab5@hwlab5:~/newfolder$ cat>file1
Hai..
This is my first program




9.Print the contents in a file
hwlab5@hwlab5:~/newfolder$ cat file1
Hai..
This is my first program

10.Copy contents into a file
hwlab5@hwlab5:~/newfolder$ cp file1 duplicate
hwlab5@hwlab5:~/newfolder$ cat duplicate
Hai..
This is my first program

hwlab5@hwlab5:~/newfolder$ ls
duplicate  file1

11.Rename a file
hwlab5@hwlab5:~/newfolder$ mv duplicate file2
hwlab5@hwlab5:~/newfolder$ ls
file1  file2

12.To get the manual page
hwlab5@hwlab5:~/newfolder$ man pwd

13.To obtain whether error is occured
hwlab5@hwlab5:~$ rm file2 2>>errorfile
hwlab5@hwlab5:~$ cat errorfile
rm: cannot remove 'file2': No such file or directory

